# MVP: test.lab.erfi.io issues its TLS cert via TSIG-authed nsupdate to our
# own Knot DNS at knot-fly-mvp on Fly anycast (169.155.56.21). End-to-end
# validated locally on 2026-05-24 against LE staging (45 s cert issuance).
# See ~/knot-fly/docs/runbooks/cf-to-knot-migration.md for the full design.
#
# `lab.erfi.io` is delegated from erfi.io at CF: `lab.erfi.io NS ns1.lab.erfi.io.`
# with glue `ns1.lab.erfi.io A 169.155.56.21`. Knot is primary for the whole
# zone. Caddy here uses RFC 2136 (caddy-dns/rfc2136 plug-in compiled into
# the image) to insert ACME `_acme-challenge.*` TXT records via TSIG.
test.lab.erfi.io {
	import tls_config_rfc2136
	encode zstd gzip
	respond "MVP — knot-fly is authoritative for *.lab.erfi.io" 200
}
